Thank you Dave for opening this channel! Judging from the community engagement so far, we’ve already got some very interesting suggestions. I’m really happy that we got the discussion going… :eco_thumbs_up:  So here is my idea:

**Eco, NFTs & incentivizing/gamifying the community**
I’m not sure if Eco has thought about finding ways for incentivizing the community in a playful manner – aside from awarding points. However, seeing that NFTs are gaining substantial traction within the crypto community, creating NFTs around Eco could be an interesting opportunity to drive community engagement through the roof and to stir it in the desired directions. Eco could create various NFTs (from simple ones of reasonable quality to really fancy, high-quality pieces of art) as an additional incentive for community members. We could also launch an NFT contest so that skillful community members could create NFTs specifically for this initiative.  These NFTs could then be used as really special awards for outstanding contributions in the community – aside from points. The incentives themselves could vary, from individual NFTs showing the team’s appreciation for something a community member did to remarkable NFT collectibles for outstanding contributions, user engagement and the like.

As an artist, I'm completely against NFTs and the "value" it drives. There's indeed traction into NFTs lately but that doesn't mean it brings value to the cryptocurrency ecosystem, IMO it's actually the opposite. It's a waste of resources and gamification to try to disguise value with media. There's absolutely no exclusivity or certificate of authenticity on an NFT.
https://youtu.be/ZIM-4Eq8A9I
https://twitter.com/neitherconfirm/status/1369285946198396928
Could it be fun? For sure but it could be misappropriated too, depending on the situation.

It's may be worth to google a little bit and research the amount of scam and damage around NFTs and what they're doing to artists and photographers all around the world, some of them quite renowned. Just an opinion, of course, it will depend on how it's executed.

We tend to focus on big actions, but often it's the small things, done consistently, over long periods of time that make long, foundational, lasting changes. Much like inculcating a new habit, or using Eco to get cashbacks and earning compounding interest over the years.

It's a little more work for the admins I guess (sorry :eco_laser: ), for smaller bounties, the community can share about the little things they do everyday to Reduce, Reuse and Recycle (R3). More people will be able to participate, and we set the stage to acknowledge the small little things people do that help maintain a clean eco-friendly environment. 

Sometimes we do the little things everyday, and we can get discouraged when we see large swathes of rubbish or groups of people who don't give a damn, so it's also a good way to way to stay motivated, knowing that there are others out there who also believe in doing the small things

Hello, eco-buds! I'd like to offer an idea for a new channel. I believe it's safe to assume that a lot of people here - like myself - are on a journey to achieve financial literacy: to understand the nature of money up to this point in time; to comprehend some of the new, exciting ways that nature seems to be changing; and, perhaps most importantly, how all of us here can help facilitate that change. Maybe some have been on this journey for awhile, but for many it's just beginning! Beginners (like myself) have likely watched some YouTube videos/documentaries, read some articles/books, Googled definitions, and maybe fallen down a rabbit hole or two :reeee:  Even after months of research, I know I've barely scratched the surface, and I'm always looking for new opportunities to learn. Education is crucial, and sharing knowledge with others is incredibly fulfilling. Which, finally, brings me to my proposal!

"Eco-cation" : a channel to share any educational resources you have acquired on this journey, any books, videos, documentaries, websites, knowledgeable people, newsletters, reliable news sources, etc. If you have a question about a definition/concept, ask it here! Eco-points could be awarded for acting as a mentor, or for sharing something valuable you've learned recently. Maybe even book reports/summaries for those that don't have the time to commit to a whole book?

These are great ideas as well, actually there are a few community members that are in the process of building out a platform that will address some of the things that you brought up! Once it is ready to be shared you should speak with them about getting involved...also maybe have a poke around the #🧮eco-nomics channel if you have some specific questions or are looking for good sources of info on a particular topic :eco_heart:

I want to propose another community bounty for the next weeks:
Geocaching! 
If people are not familiar with this: Geocaches are gps treasure hunts which mostly lead to nice or extraordinary places. Inside the Geocaches you find items which can then be traded for something else 🙂 For anyone who is interested you can find all information you need at https://www.geocaching.com !
My proposal would be that you either have to put up a Geocache yourself at a nice spot in your local area or get smaller amounts of points for completing them. 
To complete Geocaches you have to come up with a way to represent ECO and leave something inside the geocache to spread the word 🙂 

I designed and 3D-printed a small ECO-Coin which you could leave at the geocaches (see video). You can find the coin files here (for anyone who owns a 3D-Printer):

Hello, everyone!
I have one suggestion which can help to avoid some potential scams. It is about "The Accountant". Today I noticed that there are some cheaters who try to look like the bot, while actually it was a real person. You can look at example here: https://discord.com/channels/768556386404794448/817849285940215838/848126608380002304
As I understand, It is supposed to work as following: 
1) somebody checks for his points in #🏧check-your-ᵽoints 
2) Both the bot (as usual) and the scammer write information about points.
Surely, it will be not that easy to cheat somebody, because it is still easy to notice that one of "Accountants" doesn't have "BOT" badge. But still, As I understand, there is no single reason for this server to have more than 1 Accountant, which is bot.
**My suggestion: Ban immediately all the fake accountants, if you see them.**

A quick thought on a new bounty idea!

__**Suggestion:**__ New Bounty
__**Name:**__ Echo Eco
__**Background:**__ A key value held by Eco is to be inquisitive and explore new frontiers. The aim is to break the mould and challenge what we consider to be the norm. This can be seen through the premise behind the Eco App, being more than a bank or checking account, and providing unbelievable incentives for users. With the recent introduction of *Eco Academy*, Eco as a community has once again stepped into another new frontier, a new “first time”. 
**__Bounty challenge:__** Echo Eco’s sentiment by stepping out of your comfort zone and challenging yourself. This means stepping into a new frontier and doing something for the “first time”. Some ideas could be:
`-`    Learning a new skill (for example: cooking, swimming, a new language (or phrases), building something, coding, learning to draw, learning an instrument, and whatever other skills you can think of)
`-`    Participating in a new activity (for example: group sport, public speaking, volunteer work, make a scrapbook, attend a local community class)
**__Assessment:__**
`-`    Documented via photo or video and have a short written component to explain your journey and a quick explanation of what you have learned from undertaking the new skill/activity. 
`-`    Have the Eco logo somewhere in your documentation to prove that it is from the current time. 
`-`    Rewards based on quality of documentation and community vote on “favourite”  new frontiers. However, this is challenging to reward as everyone is individual and things that may challenge/are new to one person may not be for another. May have to think of another solution of rewarding points.
